headlines.description: — Doug McDermott had 28 points, Damontas Sabonis had 22 points, 11 rebounds and 10 assists, and the Indiana Pacers beat the Charlotte Hornets 116-106 on Wednesday night.

— Collin Sexton scored 29 points and Andre Drummond had 23 points, 16 rebounds and five steals against his former team, Cleveland Cavaliers to a 122-107 victory over the Detroit Pistons on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sexton scores 29 points, Cavaliers beat Pistons 122-107

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield scored a season-best 29 points, hitting hit seven 3-pointers, and the well-rested Sacramento Kings beat the Orlando Magic 121-107 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rested Kings get 29 points from Hield, defeat Magic 121-107

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 32 points and James Harden had 31 to lead a productive night for Brooklyn's big three scorers and the Nets beat the Atlanta Hawks 132-128 in overtime on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durant's 32 points lead Nets past Young, Hawks 132-128 in OT

headlines.description: — The Denver Nuggets might not want this road trip to end.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nuggets run away from short-handed Heat, 109-82

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid tried to dunk on LeBron James and instead his back slammed on the court. James’ push of the 76ers big man got him hit with a flagrant 1 and Embiid cried foul.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris shot in final seconds leads 76ers past Lakers 107-106

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 24 points, 18 rebounds and nine assists, and Donte DeVincenzo sparked a five-point sequence in the fourth quarter that helped the Milwaukee Bucks pull away for a 115-108 win over the Toronto Raptors on Wednesday night.

events.name: Boston Celtics at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan scored 21 points, Keldon Johnson had 18 points and 10 rebounds, and the San Antonio Spurs held on to beat the Boston Celtics 110-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan helps Spurs hold on to beat Celtics, 110-106

events.name: Washington Wizards at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson and Brandon Ingram each scored a season-high 32 points and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the depleted Washington Wizards 124-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, Williamson each score 32, Pelicans top Beal, Wizards

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Al Horford had 21 points and 11 rebounds, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander also scored 21 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Phoenix Suns 102-97 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder rally for 102-97 win over Suns, ruining Paul's night

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had seasons high of 29 points and 20 rebounds, Jordan Clarkson added a season-high 31 points, and the Utah Jazz beat the Dallas Mavericks 116-104 on Wednesday night for their 10th straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jazz beat Mavericks 116-104 for 10th straight victory

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Rookie center James Wiseman came off the Warriors' bench to score a career-high 25 points and dazzled opposite Minnesota No. 1 pick Anthony Edwards in a matchup of last year's top two draft selections, and Golden State swept a two-game home series...
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors beat Timberwolves 123-111 to sweep 2-game series
